        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:48PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Conrad, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Conrad.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
